caption: Amazing Indian food full of flavors, great service, very beautiful and calm atmosphere, you don't need to think twice.

The food was pipping hot! Bursting with flavor. Very neat and clean environment. Highly recommend the goat cheese naan, malai kofta and boti kabob . It is to die for! Server was a great guy had no problems explaining menu items and giving a little history on Indian food. 10 Out of 10!
I love this restaurant! Amazing amazing food. People always get take out but the dining experience is also so amazing! Great service and food, I highly recommend.
Akter was a treat! Love this place and the food was amazing
This place was so good! Akter served us and the service was amazing — such a fun time!
They have lots of goat choices.
Loved the food and the thoughtful waiter and his education of India food and wine.

Really delicious food. I tried the paneer tikka masala and malai kofta and both were awesome!
One of the best Indian restaurant in Chapel hill.
Great food at this hidden gem. Organic ingredients, vegan options (and meat!). Heated outdoor seating and very kind hosts made it with going back.
Great Drinks...Awesome food...Akhtar was very attentive and took care of us...Will definitely be back on my next trip to Raleigh...

The Chimney Indian Kitchen + Bar is an excellent restaurant and really a treat!  Mangesh is a excellent host and his bartending skill are second to none.  He is a true professional and really make your experience one of a kind.  I urge you to add this restaurant to your list.  What a way to experience North India in Chapel Hill!

They served us chicken samosa supposedly "on the house" without asking us whether we are vegetarian or not (and I am). Worst experience ever! Won't recommend. This was a gross mistake and awful service. Never visiting again.

Amazingly good food.  The biryani is the best I've had since going to India.. just the right amount of spiciness and full of flavor. The other dishes are incredibly fresh even for takeout. This is our new go-to for Indian.. it just gets better every time we eat there!

We loved it here and will definitely be back!!  The Pista Korma was excellent as was the Mango Lassi!  Our waiter, Mangesh, was great...he recommended both of those.   Garlic naan too!   You won’t be disappointed!!  I will definitely be back with more of my kids!
Really good!! Definitely recommend!
Great hospitality and great tastes  Try the cocktails.
i went here with my family and we all loved it. the food is absolutely delicious and we will definitely be going back. everything from the grill was cooked fresh.
Delicious food and friendly service.
Nice authentic Indian food...love it

This is one of the best restaurant visited in dhuram area... great food ... wonderful ambience ... recommend for people ... started with nice cocktail ( river water)... then moved to paneer and malai kofta... all dishes were tasty.... praveen from restaurant assisted Us very well..

Wonderful! My husband thought the medium could be spicier, but I thought it was perfect, so hot for him next time!
Excellent flavors. The complexity and depth of the flavors really sets this place apart.
Always high quality, fresh and amazing food. Try the Chettinad Masala!
Owned by amazing people who work hard to ensure customers have a wonderful experience!

Chicken Tikka Masala was amazing here. Staff members were very attentive. Would definitely recommend.

We were blown away by our recent dinner at Chimney Kitchen. Not only were the food and presentation visually stunning, the flavors were next-level delicious. And the service allowed us to enjoy our meal with just the right amount of attention. Definitely will return!

I had an amazing dinner here. The food tasted delicious, came out quickly, and looked beautiful too. The restaurant was really clean and I felt safe eating inside even during the pandemic. I will be back!

This was a really great experience right in the middle of CoVid.  We felt safe and comfortable dining inside.  The service was attentive, the decor is clean yet eclectic, and the food was AMAZING! Excited to find this gem.
Excellent channa masala and tiki masala. Friendly staff! Thank you!
Excellent staff and food is delicious. The prices are great. Will definitely be going back because it was so relaxing.

Excellent food and delicious. Great customer service. Great place to come and relax and enjoy your food in peace. The food has the perfect amount of spices. Great people. Will definitely be going back to enjoy the good food and hospitality.
The dish I had was amazing. I loved it. I will definitely be going back.

We had take out from here a few days ago and it was delicious! The host made sure we had plates and cutlery so we could eat outside. It was quick and the food is all scratch made as you can see from the whole spices (rather than a premade mix) in the curry.

Love all of the dishes at Chimney. Excellent service. Quality food  and great bar. I enjoyed the lobster dish and shrimp. My husband loves the lamb chops and even the vegetarian dishes are DELICIOUS!!!! I give them five stars!!!! Highly Recommended. A great date night restaurant

Love all of the dishes at Chimney. Excellent service. Quality food  and great bar. I enjoyed the lobster dish and shrimp. My husband loves the lamb chops and even the vegetarian dishes are DELICIOUS!!!! I give them five stars!!!! Highly Recommended

Lovely new, nice Indian restaurant. Takes time 4 either a takeout or eat in order, because it's not exactly fast food. However, worth the wait. Many northern Indian dishes. Yummy naan. Many vegetarian choices. Nice people, nice staff.

Best Indian food in the area, it has now become my go-to for delivery whenever I want to order out (although the restaurant itself is also very nice). I’ve now eaten from the restaurant multiple times and never been disappointed with anything I’ve ordered!
What amazing food, quality was still far above expectation despite the fact we had to order takeout due to the quarantine.  Definitely give Chimney a call!
Delicate North Indian food with lots of main entrees and desert varieties. Price is very reasonable and quality of food is excellent.

By far best northern AND southern Indian restaurant in the Triangle. Phenomenal and unique.
Amazing tasting Indian food!
Amazing lunch buffet!

Lots of good vegetarian options. Delicious naan. Clean place with a good atmosphere.

Second time coming to this place, fantastic experience very good quality food, excellent service, prices are nice as well. Will be a regular spot to stop and enjoy some good quality food.
I and my wife ate the there on Wed (1/15/20). We were very happy with the service and the quality of the food.

Easily the best Indian place at Chapel Hill that I've tried. Under 12 Dollars for all you can eat, fantastic Indian food is a pretty easy sell not gonna lie.
Great restaurant. I ordered chicken vindaloo and french fries. I liked them both.
